# Purpose: Ignore local runtime data, caches and developer-specific files.
# Input/Output: Git reads this file to decide which generated files stay local only.
# Invariants: Source code and documentation stay versioned, secrets and runtime state do not.
# Debug: If a file is missing from Git unexpectedly, check whether it matches one of these patterns.

.env
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.DS_Store

backend/.pytest_cache/
backend/.coverage

data/
postgres-data/

